LAFIA – As the ruling All Progressive Congress (APC), national convention has come and gone a group under the aegis of Migili Cultural and Development Association a (MCDA) a social cultural on Monday hailed President Muhammadu Buhari’s maturity for the choice of former governor of Nasarawa State Senator Abdullahi Adamu, as the chairman of national Working Committee of the party. The group made their position known in a press statement signed by Dr. Philip Ajeh, the president of Migili Cultural Development Association (MCDA), and made available to DAILY INDEPENDENT in Lafia the State capital. The statement said that the maturity exhibited by President Muhammadu Buhari, that led to the success of the convention was commendable. The group also commended governor Abdullahi Sule, for the fatherly leadership role he played between the two former governors of Nasarawa State who were aspirants for the same position. The statement read, ” We want to also commend senator Tanko Al-makura for been a dogged politician and for accepting the wishes of the party. ” The Migili Cultural and development Association are happy with senator Abdullahi Adamu for being crowned the National Chairman of APC . “The Migili nation want to recollect with nostalgia that senator Abdullahi Adamu exhibited tremendous concerns and interest to the Migili nation in Nasarawa State during his tenure as the governor of Nasarawa State,” the statement read. The group also mentioned some laudable legacies of former governor on education sector to include: establishment of tertiary institution, namely Nasarawa State University Keffi, College of Education Akwanga , Nasarawa State Polytechnic Lafia, now Mustapha polytechnic Lafia, and others. POLL Dr. Ajeh Philip called on the Migili people to support the government of governor Abdullahi Sule, for the dividend of democracy strive in the area.